Melt the butter in a saucepan over a medium heat.Stir in the brown sugar and milk, and bring to the boil for 2-3 minutes, without stirring.Remove from the heat, and stir in the peanut butter and vanilla seeds.Place the icing sugar in a large bowl, and pour the hot butter and sugar mixture on top. Using a wooden spoon, beat the mixture until smooth.Pour into a 20cm/8in square baking tray, and set aside to cool slightly, then place in the fridge to chill completely.Cut the fudge into squares with a sharp knife, turn out of the tin and store in an airtight container.